A brand-new universal access mat has been rolled out, creating a pathway at Muizenberg beach to guide wheelchairs and other walking-aid users closer to the ocean action in minutes. CAPE TOWN - People with physical disabilities now have easier access to Cape Town's beaches. The pilot programme has been launched at Muizenberg beach. This also coincided with International Wheelchair Day. READ: Disabled drivers take the wheel This beach is known for its famous surf spots. But it’s not been easy for wheelchair-bound beachgoers to get access -- until now. A brand new universal access mat has been rolled out, creating a pathway that guides wheelchairs and other walking-aid users, closer to the ocean action in minutes. While the project is being piloted here, there are bigger plans ahead.